00908     struct scan_set_relop {
00909       scan_set_relop(ParserState &state, int relop)
00910         : state(state), relop(relop) { }
00911       void operator()(char const *str, char const *end) const {
00912         process();
00913       }
00914       void operator()(const char c) const {
00915         process();
00916       }
00917       void process() const {
00918         if (state.scan.current_timestamp_set) {
00919           switch (relop) {
00920           case RELOP_EQ:
00921             if (state.scan.start_time_set || state.scan.end_time_set)
00922               HT_THROW(Error::HQL_PARSE_ERROR, "Bad timestamp expression");
00923             state.scan.set_time_interval(state.scan.current_timestamp,
00924                                          state.scan.current_timestamp);
00925             break;
00926           case RELOP_GT:
00927             if (state.scan.end_time_set ||
00928                 (state.scan.start_time_set &&
00929                  state.scan.start_time() >= state.scan.current_timestamp))
00930               HT_THROW(Error::HQL_PARSE_ERROR, "Bad timestamp expression");
00931             state.scan.set_end_time(state.scan.current_timestamp);
00932             break;
00933           case RELOP_GE:
00934             if (state.scan.end_time_set ||
00935                 (state.scan.start_time_set &&
00936                  state.scan.start_time() > state.scan.current_timestamp))
00937               HT_THROW(Error::HQL_PARSE_ERROR, "Bad timestamp expression");
00938             state.scan.set_end_time(state.scan.current_timestamp + 1);
00939             break;
00940           case RELOP_LT:
00941             if (state.scan.start_time_set ||
00942                 (state.scan.end_time_set &&
00943                  state.scan.start_time() <= (state.scan.current_timestamp + 1)))
00944               HT_THROW(Error::HQL_PARSE_ERROR, "Bad timestamp expression");
00945             state.scan.set_start_time(state.scan.current_timestamp + 1);
00946             break;
00947           case RELOP_LE:
00948             if (state.scan.start_time_set ||
00949                 (state.scan.end_time_set &&
00950                  state.scan.end_time() <= state.scan.current_timestamp))
00951               HT_THROW(Error::HQL_PARSE_ERROR, "Bad timestamp expression");
00952             state.scan.set_start_time(state.scan.current_timestamp);
00953             break;
00954           case RELOP_SW:
00955             HT_THROW(Error::HQL_PARSE_ERROR, "Bad timestamp operator (=^)");
00956           }
00957           state.scan.current_timestamp_set = false;
00958           state.scan.current_relop = 0;
00959         }
00960         else if (state.scan.current_rowkey_set) {
00961           HT_ASSERT(state.scan.current_rowkey_set);
00962 
00963           switch (relop) {
00964           case RELOP_EQ:
00965             state.scan.current_ri.set_start(state.scan.current_rowkey, true);
00966             state.scan.current_ri.set_end(state.scan.current_rowkey, true);
00967             break;
00968           case RELOP_LT:
00969             state.scan.current_ri.set_start(state.scan.current_rowkey, false);
00970             break;
00971           case RELOP_LE:
00972             state.scan.current_ri.set_start(state.scan.current_rowkey, true);
00973             break;
00974           case RELOP_GT:
00975             state.scan.current_ri.set_end(state.scan.current_rowkey, false);
00976             break;
00977           case RELOP_GE:
00978             state.scan.current_ri.set_end(state.scan.current_rowkey, true);
00979             break;
00980           case RELOP_SW:
00981             HT_THROW(Error::HQL_PARSE_ERROR, "Bad use of operator (=^)");
00982           }
00983           state.scan.current_rowkey_set = false;
00984           state.scan.current_relop = 0;
00985         }
00986         else if (state.scan.current_cell_row.size()
00987                  && state.scan.current_ci.empty()) {
00988           String &row = state.scan.current_cell_row;
00989           String &column = state.scan.current_cell_column;
00990 
00991           switch (relop) {
00992           case RELOP_EQ:
00993             state.scan.current_ci.set_start(row, column, true);
00994             state.scan.current_ci.set_end(row, column, true);
00995             break;
00996           case RELOP_LT:
00997             state.scan.current_ci.set_start(row, column, false);
00998             break;
00999           case RELOP_LE:
01000             state.scan.current_ci.set_start(row, column, true);
01001             break;
01002           case RELOP_GT:
01003             state.scan.current_ci.set_end(row, column, false);
01004             break;
01005           case RELOP_GE:
01006             state.scan.current_ci.set_end(row, column, true);
01007           case RELOP_SW:
01008             HT_THROW(Error::HQL_PARSE_ERROR, "Bad use of operator (=^)");
01009           }
01010           row.clear();
01011           column.clear();
01012           state.scan.current_relop = 0;
01013         }
01014         else
01015           state.scan.current_relop = relop;
01016       }
01017       ParserState &state;
01018       int relop;
01019     };

01196         state.delete_time = (uint64_t)t * 1000000000LL + state.nanoseconds;
01197         memset(&state.tmval, 0, sizeof(state.tmval));
01198         state.nanoseconds = 0;
01199       }
01200       ParserState &state;
01201     };

01203     struct set_scanner_id {
01204       set_scanner_id(ParserState &state) : state(state) { }
01205       void operator()(char const *str, char const *end) const {
01206         state.scanner_id = (uint32_t)strtol(str, 0, 10);
01207       }
01208       ParserState &state;
01209     };
